cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the challenges and solutions for designing embedded computing systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also highly relevant as the paper focuses on integrating feedback control and real-time computing. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the design methodology for achieving better system performance. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses scheduling and resource allocation in computing systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of designing computing systems in unpredictable environments.
